  "short_text": "Count Unique Names",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a string `S` containing space-separated strings from the user and forms a set from these strings. The program should then print the number of unique strings in the set.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing space-separated strings to form the set.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be a single integer, which represents the number of unique strings in the set.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the input is:\n\n```\napple banana apple orange banana\n```\n\nThe output should be:\n\n```\n3\n```\n\nThis is because the unique strings in the input are **apple, banana,** and **orange**.",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "f152521e-2701-4dbe-9c03-ccb7049516c0",
      "code_content": "s = input().strip().split()\nunique_items = set(s)\nprint(len(unique_items))\n",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
